    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset represents a 4-level hierarchical structure with categorical parents (geography \u2192 accident type \u2192 vehicle category) and quantitative values (fatality counts). Original data from IIHS demonstrates strong right-skew distribution (\u03bc=2886, \u03c3=2721) with urban pedestrians forming the largest single cohort. The sunburst visualization maximizes data-ink ratio by using arc lengths for quantities and color brightness for hierarchy depth. Cairo's principles are applied through: 1) Pre-attentive color intensity variations for category levels 2) Proportional area encoding matching human area perception 3) Interactive drill-down maintaining spatial relationships. Border contrast (3px black) and label filtering (minimum arc length thresholds) prevent visual clutter while preserving information density."
